Program: Start the Week
Title: Science Fiction
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b04prcsg
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 24 Nov 2014
Tom Sutcliffe explores our relationship with computer technology and the interplay of alien and familiar in science fiction. Tom's joined in the studio by writer William Gibson, novelist Michel Faber, LSE Professor Judy Wajcman and historian Dominic Sandbrook. How have computer technologies transformed our sense of outer space, cyber space and our own inner space? Producer: Simon Tillotson. Show less